OL,3,CDebate to ban Jersey landlords from
OL,4,Cdiscriminating against pet-owners
OL,6,F"It is the preferred method that
OL,7,Flandlords use their own discretion
OL,8,Fbecause some units are probably not
OL,9,Fsuitable for animals."
OL,11,FDeputy Andrews also argued that fears
OL,12,Fof pet-related damage, noise, and
OL,13,Fincreased neighbourhood tension are
OL,14,Fvalid reasons for a landlord to ban
OL,15,Fpets from their properties.
OL,17,FThe Jersey Landlords' Association
OL,18,Fagrees that "Deputy Curtis'
OL,19,Fproposition is high on aspiration and
OL,20,Flow on detail".
